1
00:00:20,170 --> 00:00:23,120
Thado Minsaw of Inwa lost the battle.

2
00:00:24,160 --> 00:00:27,920
There is no relationship between you and the Crown Prince anymore.

3
00:00:30,490 --> 00:00:32,120
Do you remember our lesson in sword?

4
00:00:32,191 --> 00:00:34,470
When I wanted to stop practicing, I'd tell you like this.

5
00:00:38,457 --> 00:00:39,458
Withdraw!

6
00:00:40,137 --> 00:00:42,520
Think about your action,

7
00:00:42,577 --> 00:00:44,080
what was the wrong thing you to me and to Hongsawadi?

8
00:00:45,203 --> 00:00:46,280
She is not coming back.

9
00:00:46,597 --> 00:00:48,240
How can a mother

10
00:00:48,640 --> 00:00:50,360
leave her child behind?

11
00:00:51,090 --> 00:00:52,480
This is how the wars work.

12
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:54,400
Only commoners are dead

13
00:00:54,560 --> 00:00:55,800
not the rulers.

14
00:00:55,943 --> 00:00:59,440
After the royal wedding, the Crown Prince

15
00:00:59,760 --> 00:01:01,600
needs to recruit his soldiers, to

16
00:01:01,937 --> 00:01:03,960
march and fight against Ayutthaya.

17
00:01:06,477 --> 00:01:08,520
We are outnumbered, their soldiers are so much more than ours.

18
00:01:08,810 --> 00:01:10,960
We need to attack them when they are least expected.

19
00:01:11,356 --> 00:01:12,483
I will lead the troops.

20
00:01:12,920 --> 00:01:13,921
You can't!

21
00:01:14,800 --> 00:01:17,720
If I stay behind, just to give orders, the soldiers won't dare to march forward.

22
00:01:18,280 --> 00:01:19,320
You all need to watch me!

23
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,841
Follow my lead and that is my command.

24
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,401
Yes, Your Highness.

25
00:01:51,437 --> 00:01:52,438
Shoot!

26
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:18,361
Have the troops disperse into small units

27
00:02:18,490 --> 00:02:20,560
and attack from every direction.

28
00:02:20,597 --> 00:02:21,720
Do not remain gathered together.

29
00:02:23,598 --> 00:02:24,599
Yes, Your Highness.

30
00:02:36,137 --> 00:02:37,400
Follow me.

31
00:03:26,617 --> 00:03:27,618
Prince Nares.

32
00:03:55,803 --> 00:03:58,800
Prince Nares descends into battle, leading his troops

33
00:03:59,083 --> 00:04:01,160
without any fear of death or regard for his own life.

34
00:04:02,097 --> 00:04:03,097
It is no wonder

35
00:04:04,963 --> 00:04:07,400
the morale of the Ayutthaya soldiers is so formidable.

36
00:05:34,597 --> 00:05:36,360
King Nanda Bayin

37
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,760
has besieged us

38
00:05:40,337 --> 00:05:42,080
for more than two months now.

39
00:05:43,960 --> 00:05:45,640
The city walls remain sturdy,

40
00:05:45,757 --> 00:05:47,840
and the provisions are still plentiful.

41
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,760
Do not be so concerned, Your Majesty.

42
00:05:53,230 --> 00:05:54,750
Our troops

43
00:05:56,037 --> 00:05:58,160
are many times fewer than Hongsawadi's.

44
00:06:00,010 --> 00:06:01,720
Nares must not be careless.

45
00:06:02,650 --> 00:06:03,480
Do not worry, Father.

46
00:06:04,440 --> 00:06:05,920
Nares knows we are outnumbered,

47
00:06:06,830 --> 00:06:10,120
so he avoids engaging in prolonged combat

48
00:06:11,650 --> 00:06:13,640
and instead conducts intermittent guerrilla warfare.

49
00:06:36,297 --> 00:06:37,800
We send men in to burn their supplies,

50
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,480
plunder their camps,

51
00:06:41,203 --> 00:06:42,920
and harass them so they get no rest or sleep.

52
00:06:45,417 --> 00:06:47,120
Hey, help put out the fire!

53
00:06:56,520 --> 00:06:57,521
Now,

54
00:06:58,320 --> 00:07:00,240
the Hongsawadi troops are beginning to starve.

55
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:03,240
Many are weak and fallen ill.

56
00:07:05,777 --> 00:07:09,240
You were born and raised in Phitsanulok, so you may not know.

57
00:07:14,703 --> 00:07:18,200
The lands surrounding Ayutthaya are low-lying plains.

58
00:07:20,840 --> 00:07:22,360
Whenever the rains fall,

59
00:07:24,243 --> 00:07:26,800
there will be flooding for months on end.

60
00:07:28,930 --> 00:07:31,400
the Hongsawadi army will not be able to remain.

61
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:36,320
Tell Nares to be patient

62
00:07:37,800 --> 00:07:39,440
and hold his ground in this battle.

63
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:42,520
When the rains arrive,

64
00:07:44,803 --> 00:07:46,760
Victory shall be ours.

65
00:08:12,450 --> 00:08:13,451
The rainy season has arrived.

66
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:20,360
It has rained heavily for three days and three nights.

67
00:08:31,080 --> 00:08:34,880
The fields outside the Ayutthaya city walls are flooded.

68
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:38,160
Hongsawadi can no longer maintain its camp.

69
00:08:48,843 --> 00:08:51,720
On the 10th day of the waxing moon, the 6th month,

70
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:56,140
King Nanda Bayin was forced to withdraw his army.

71
00:09:05,217 --> 00:09:06,880
This defeat

72
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:10,000
caused him great distress and resentment.

73
00:09:32,640 --> 00:09:34,520
Hongsawadi has lost many men.

74
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:38,640
King Nanda Bayin will likely need to rest to conscript more troops

75
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:39,920
and gather supplies.

76
00:09:40,881 --> 00:09:43,240
Ayutthaya will be free from war for at least two years.

77
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:48,160
During this time, I will hasten the people to plant rice and store up provisions.

78
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:51,530
I will handle the training of the new recruits myself.

79
00:09:51,710 --> 00:09:52,711
Do not be concerned, Father.

80
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:00,600
There is still one more matter

81
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:03,520
that weighs heavily on my heart.

82
00:10:06,870 --> 00:10:08,240
About Suphankalaya.

83
00:10:18,423 --> 00:10:19,424
Father.

84
00:10:24,807 --> 00:10:25,808
- Father!
- Father!

85
00:10:26,303 --> 00:10:27,304
- Father!
- Father!

86
00:10:30,590 --> 00:10:31,591
Father.

87
00:10:33,697 --> 00:10:34,698
Father.

88
00:10:35,017 --> 00:10:36,600
Summon the royal physician here.

89
00:10:38,018 --> 00:10:39,019
Quickly!

90
00:10:55,283 --> 00:10:56,284
Dam.

91
00:10:57,780 --> 00:10:58,781
Khao.

92
00:11:06,830 --> 00:11:09,200
Perhaps it is best to rest, Your Majesty?

93
00:11:09,720 --> 00:11:11,240
Feeling unwell like this,

94
00:11:11,970 --> 00:11:13,080
what do you intend to do?

95
00:11:15,337 --> 00:11:17,880
It is because I am bedridden that I have realized this.

96
00:11:21,690 --> 00:11:24,440
If we must prepare for a great battle once again,

97
00:11:26,130 --> 00:11:27,720
when will you be ready?

98
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:31,800
Training the new recruits will take no more than a year, Your Majesty.

99
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:34,361
But the previous war

100
00:11:35,010 --> 00:11:36,880
has caused great damage to our fields and granaries.

101
00:11:38,270 --> 00:11:39,360
As for the provisions…

102
00:11:43,557 --> 00:11:45,000
We will need two years, Your Majesty.

103
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,440
We must expand the rice fields,

104
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:51,840
grow more crops, and build granaries to stockpile provisions.

105
00:11:53,937 --> 00:11:55,000
Then make haste.

106
00:11:59,457 --> 00:12:00,480
Whenever you are ready,

107
00:12:01,520 --> 00:12:02,760
Let me know.

108
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,600
What do you intend to do, Your Majesty?

109
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:17,801
bring Suphankalaya

110
00:12:20,730 --> 00:12:23,000
back to you, of course.

111
00:12:27,800 --> 00:12:29,760
Did you think I did not see you

112
00:12:31,510 --> 00:12:33,240
secretly weeping for our child?

113
00:12:59,190 --> 00:13:01,360
Now, Min Letya,

114
00:13:01,843 --> 00:13:04,080
the Lord of Inwa, has passed away.

115
00:13:05,160 --> 00:13:06,600
As Inwa is a great city

116
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,120
crucial to the stability of Hongsawadi,

117
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:13,760
I hereby appoint Minye Kyawswa

118
00:13:14,117 --> 00:13:16,760
to be the King of Inwa from this day forth.

119
00:13:35,412 --> 00:13:39,000
It is a great royal grace, Your Majesty.

120
00:14:13,170 --> 00:14:14,171
Take it all.

121
00:14:15,200 --> 00:14:16,201
Go.

122
00:14:19,883 --> 00:14:21,400
Take good care of my belongings.

123
00:14:24,243 --> 00:14:25,244
Brother.

124
00:14:27,050 --> 00:14:28,360
Will you depart tomorrow?

125
00:14:31,770 --> 00:14:32,800
Why should I stay?

126
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,760
Being the ruler in Inwa

127
00:14:36,563 --> 00:14:38,410
is better than staying in Hongsawadi

128
00:14:39,923 --> 00:14:42,400
and always remaining subordinate to Mingyi Swa.

129
00:14:45,763 --> 00:14:47,700
- Take it all.
- Yes, Your Highness.

130
00:14:59,050 --> 00:15:00,051
Mingyi Hnaung.

131
00:15:02,170 --> 00:15:03,800
You staying here alone,

132
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,681
do not just eat and sleep.

133
00:15:07,100 --> 00:15:08,640
Be the eyes and ears for Father as well.

134
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,800
I do not trust our elder brother,

135
00:15:14,760 --> 00:15:17,360
who values outsiders more than his own kin.

136
00:15:28,743 --> 00:15:32,320
The various cities, large and small, under the power of Hongsawadi

137
00:15:32,543 --> 00:15:33,720
have begun to rebel.

138
00:15:34,560 --> 00:15:36,000
King Nanda Bayin,

139
00:15:36,520 --> 00:15:38,521
therefore, had to hasten the strengthening of ties

140
00:15:38,960 --> 00:15:40,561
with the various vassal lords.

141
00:15:44,170 --> 00:15:46,297
Thus, he bestowed Min A Htwe

142
00:15:46,870 --> 00:15:49,440
in marriage to Lord Kaolad,

143
00:15:49,960 --> 00:15:51,800
a descendant of the Shan prince,

144
00:15:53,880 --> 00:15:58,201
and ordered her to follow Minye Kyawswa to reside in Inwa.

145
00:16:03,103 --> 00:16:07,400
This brought boundless sorrow to Sister.

146
00:16:15,977 --> 00:16:18,880
As for me, I prepared the troops

147
00:16:21,983 --> 00:16:23,960
and stockpiled provisions

148
00:16:24,560 --> 00:16:26,000
for the great battle

149
00:16:27,103 --> 00:16:28,520
that was soon to come.

150
00:16:39,057 --> 00:16:41,200
There is a message from the Queen Mother, Your Highness.

151
00:17:15,083 --> 00:17:17,084
Father is gravely ill.

152
00:17:17,840 --> 00:17:19,680
The royal physicians are providing treatment,

153
00:17:20,200 --> 00:17:22,800
but his condition only remains stable or worsens.

154
00:17:23,677 --> 00:17:26,640
He desires to see your face one last time.

155
00:17:27,600 --> 00:17:31,080
Princess Suphankalaya, please hasten your return.

156
00:17:31,840 --> 00:17:35,480
If you delay, it may be too late.

157
00:18:31,183 --> 00:18:33,600
The contents of that message are but a ruse.

158
00:18:35,910 --> 00:18:39,520
Father and I are merely finding a way for you to return to Ayutthaya.

159
00:18:40,560 --> 00:18:42,360
You must send word to Suphankalaya,

160
00:18:42,900 --> 00:18:46,200
informing her that I am gravely ill and wishes for her to return for a final farewell.

161
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:49,440
Why do you speak such words? They are most inauspicious.

162
00:18:50,641 --> 00:18:53,680
It is but a ruse of war. Why take offense at such things?

163
00:18:56,377 --> 00:18:57,680
I understand.

164
00:18:58,197 --> 00:18:59,920
No matter how suspicious they may be,

165
00:19:00,123 --> 00:19:02,240
if a child asks to return for a father's final breath,

166
00:19:02,623 --> 00:19:04,160
they must surely allow her to return.

167
00:19:07,077 --> 00:19:08,560
But they certainly will not allow it.

168
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,700
If they do not allow it, then we fight.

169
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,481
Once we have the hostage back,

170
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:16,320
If war it is, so be it. I fear it not.

171
00:19:24,403 --> 00:19:25,560
And this time,

172
00:19:26,160 --> 00:19:29,040
you shall never have to return to Hongsawadi again.

173
00:19:54,203 --> 00:19:55,240
When shall you depart?

174
00:19:56,990 --> 00:19:58,600
If it is your royal command,

175
00:19:59,703 --> 00:20:01,760
I shall depart immediately, Your Majesty.

176
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,041
Your Majesty,

177
00:20:09,983 --> 00:20:13,040
showing gratitude toward one’s parents is of the utmost importance.

178
00:20:16,410 --> 00:20:17,657
Should she be barred from going,

179
00:20:18,837 --> 00:20:21,760
anyone who learns of it would surely find cause for criticism.

180
00:20:30,838 --> 00:20:31,840
Phraya Chanto.

181
00:20:33,963 --> 00:20:37,720
Have the troops guard the royal procession well.

182
00:20:38,570 --> 00:20:40,760
Ensure no harm befalls them along the way.

183
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,121
Yes, Your Majesty.

184
00:20:43,721 --> 00:20:45,160
Your kindness is most gracious, Your Majesty.

185
00:21:16,943 --> 00:21:17,944
Jeep.

186
00:21:19,063 --> 00:21:22,320
Prepare yourselves to return to Ayutthaya. Help me gather our belongings.

187
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:24,681
How much should we take with us, Your Highness?

188
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:28,082
Everything of importance, everything of value,

189
00:21:30,360 --> 00:21:31,361
carry it all away.

190
00:21:32,317 --> 00:21:33,318
Yes, Your Highness.

191
00:21:51,560 --> 00:21:53,161
Mother, Father.

192
00:21:53,920 --> 00:21:55,560
Dam, what is the matter?

193
00:21:55,670 --> 00:21:56,671
You are making quite a noise.

194
00:22:00,217 --> 00:22:01,880
A fast courier from Hongsawadi has arrived with news.

195
00:22:03,557 --> 00:22:05,000
I am finally going home.

196
00:22:05,960 --> 00:22:06,961
What?

197
00:22:08,070 --> 00:22:10,760
Do you hear?

198
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:13,081
Our child is coming home.

199
00:22:22,923 --> 00:22:24,520
Our child is coming home at last.

200
00:23:07,483 --> 00:23:09,117
Escort the royal procession, quickly!

201
00:23:10,710 --> 00:23:13,080
Phraya Chanto, what is the matter?

202
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:16,401
Your Highness, we are under ambush.

203
00:23:22,190 --> 00:23:23,717
Retreat! Fall back!

204
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:25,001
Wait a moment.

205
00:23:25,003 --> 00:23:26,920
- Retreat the army back to Hongsawadi.
- Wait!

206
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,921
- Stop!
- Go!

207
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,501
Where are you retreating to?

208
00:23:33,123 --> 00:23:34,240
Stop this now.

209
00:23:43,757 --> 00:23:44,758
Father.

210
00:23:49,050 --> 00:23:51,360
- What is the matter?
- The royal procession is under ambush.

211
00:23:54,043 --> 00:23:55,840
Phraya Chanto feared there might be traitors,

212
00:23:56,397 --> 00:23:59,640
so he has invited Princess Suphankalaya to return to Hongsawadi, Your Majesty.

213
00:24:06,037 --> 00:24:07,038
Good.

214
00:24:08,423 --> 00:24:09,524
Well done.

215
00:24:12,440 --> 00:24:13,760
But I still have doubts.

216
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:17,663
why do you

217
00:24:17,743 --> 00:24:21,317
not allow Princess Suphankalaya to return to Ayutthaya?

218
00:24:26,643 --> 00:24:29,400
She is the heart and soul of Ayutthaya.

219
00:24:33,523 --> 00:24:35,040
If she were to return,

220
00:24:36,190 --> 00:24:38,360
they would surely be filled with joy.

221
00:24:44,590 --> 00:24:46,880
But since they are my enemies,

222
00:24:47,697 --> 00:24:49,698
let them not hope for such happiness.

223
00:25:11,397 --> 00:25:12,398
Father, Mother,

224
00:25:13,977 --> 00:25:15,300
Sister cannot come anymore.

225
00:25:18,730 --> 00:25:19,731
What?

226
00:25:20,543 --> 00:25:21,544
Along the way,

227
00:25:22,280 --> 00:25:25,300
forest bandits raided the procession, so they had to turn back.

228
00:25:28,317 --> 00:25:31,320
Sunday, the 13th day of the waning moon,

229
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,360
the 8th month, the year of the tiger,

230
00:25:36,963 --> 00:25:39,520
King Maha Thammaracha

231
00:25:41,040 --> 00:25:42,680
has deceased.

232
00:26:17,197 --> 00:26:19,160
Prince Nares,

233
00:26:19,877 --> 00:26:21,640
ascends the throne,

234
00:26:23,040 --> 00:26:24,080
reigning under the name

235
00:26:24,760 --> 00:26:27,840
Somdet Phra Borommabat Bongkot Lak

236
00:26:28,123 --> 00:26:29,880
Akara Burisodom

237
00:26:30,610 --> 00:26:33,680
Boromma Nor Nara, Chao Fa Nares,

238
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:35,480
the supreme elder brother.

239
00:26:37,170 --> 00:26:39,040
Long live the King.

240
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:41,601
On this occasion,

241
00:26:42,201 --> 00:26:44,202
His Majesty the King

242
00:26:44,950 --> 00:26:48,360
hereby appoints Prince Ekathosarot,

243
00:26:49,417 --> 00:26:52,680
his royal younger brother,

244
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:55,160
to the rank of

245
00:26:55,920 --> 00:26:59,960
Phra Bat Somdet Phra Ekathosarut Isuan

246
00:27:00,640 --> 00:27:03,720
Borommanat Bophit Phra Phuttha Chao Yu Hua,

247
00:27:06,200 --> 00:27:07,760
bestowing upon him authority

248
00:27:08,880 --> 00:27:11,881
equal to that of the sovereign in every respect.

249
00:27:17,150 --> 00:27:19,151
Long live the King.

250
00:28:05,057 --> 00:28:06,058
You all wait here.

251
00:28:07,560 --> 00:28:08,561
Yes, Your Majesty.

252
00:28:40,770 --> 00:28:41,771
Brother.

253
00:28:42,680 --> 00:28:43,681
No, Brother.

254
00:28:46,110 --> 00:28:47,111
No need to.

255
00:28:52,400 --> 00:28:53,401
at the very least,

256
00:28:55,023 --> 00:28:56,840
I should be able to offer my blessings.

257
00:29:12,024 --> 00:29:15,025
At this place, at this time,

258
00:29:16,190 --> 00:29:19,600
Elder brother is elder brother, and younger brother is younger brother.

259
00:29:22,917 --> 00:29:24,190
I beg your forgiveness.

260
00:29:27,650 --> 00:29:30,520
As for Sister, there is nothing I can do.

261
00:29:33,017 --> 00:29:34,720
King Nanda Bayin

262
00:29:35,330 --> 00:29:36,880
has treated us as enemies.

263
00:29:37,560 --> 00:29:39,960
We can no longer live under the same sky. What say you?

264
00:29:49,345 --> 00:29:51,446
I have fled from myself for long enough.

265
00:29:55,120 --> 00:29:56,200
I am my father's son,

266
00:30:01,083 --> 00:30:03,300
the Crown Prince of Hongsawadi.

267
00:30:16,440 --> 00:30:18,560
It is a duty I have carried since birth.

268
00:30:23,720 --> 00:30:24,760
Whether I like it or not,

269
00:30:27,600 --> 00:30:29,360
it cannot be changed to anything else.

270
00:30:45,560 --> 00:30:47,200
Duty is like the mist

271
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:50,401
that obscures the sun.

272
00:30:56,757 --> 00:30:58,600
The prayers of us both,

273
00:31:02,303 --> 00:31:03,840
therefore, can never come true.

274
00:31:18,510 --> 00:31:19,511
Today,

275
00:31:22,597 --> 00:31:23,760
I come to bid you farewell.

276
00:31:46,630 --> 00:31:47,631
The two of us

277
00:31:50,410 --> 00:31:51,760
meeting here,

278
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:55,001
this time,

279
00:31:57,957 --> 00:31:59,120
shall be the last.

280
00:32:10,103 --> 00:32:11,124
From this moment forth,

281
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:14,480
we shall each fulfill our own duty.

282
00:32:51,360 --> 00:32:52,680
The oath we once took,

283
00:32:56,450 --> 00:32:58,237
that neither of us would harm the other,

284
00:33:02,823 --> 00:33:05,124
I hereby renounce.

285
00:33:09,857 --> 00:33:10,858
From this day forward,

286
00:33:12,920 --> 00:33:14,080
should we ever meet,

287
00:33:16,350 --> 00:33:17,360
let neither of us

288
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,800
stay our hand.

289
00:34:02,977 --> 00:34:06,160
News of Hongsawadi's defeat by Ayutthaya

290
00:34:07,080 --> 00:34:09,320
has caused the various vassal states

291
00:34:10,240 --> 00:34:11,640
to rise in rebellion.

292
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,121
Your Majesty, the lord of Muang Kong,

293
00:34:17,377 --> 00:34:19,200
-[Sirichai Noratha, the minister.]
- taking Prince Nares as his example

294
00:34:19,443 --> 00:34:20,760
has incited a rebellion, Your Majesty.

295
00:34:23,110 --> 00:34:25,480
Let Minye Kyawswa lead the army to suppress them.

296
00:34:26,570 --> 00:34:30,920
The King of Inwa at this time must defend the city of Inwa

297
00:34:31,360 --> 00:34:33,480
to secure the front against the Shan states

298
00:34:33,547 --> 00:34:35,040
and prevent further defiance, Your Majesty.

299
00:34:35,703 --> 00:34:38,120
As for the King of Taungoo, he is gravely ill

300
00:34:38,323 --> 00:34:39,680
and has not attended to state affairs

301
00:34:39,817 --> 00:34:42,000
for many months now, Your Majesty.

302
00:34:42,318 --> 00:34:43,319
Blast it!

303
00:34:47,950 --> 00:34:51,200
In times of hardship, there is no one I can rely on.

304
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,321
Mingyi Hnaung.

305
00:34:55,890 --> 00:34:56,891
Yes, Your Majesty.

306
00:34:57,120 --> 00:34:58,960
I hereby appoint you as commander

307
00:34:59,510 --> 00:35:00,960
to lead an army of one hundred thousand

308
00:35:01,123 --> 00:35:02,760
to suppress the rebellion of Muang Kong in our stead.

309
00:35:03,680 --> 00:35:05,000
I humbly accept your royal command, Your Majesty.

310
00:35:09,040 --> 00:35:10,320
As for Ayutthaya,

311
00:35:12,657 --> 00:35:13,880
if left unchecked,

312
00:35:14,637 --> 00:35:16,881
other cities will follow its example without end.

313
00:35:22,756 --> 00:35:24,040
Crown Prince,

314
00:35:28,283 --> 00:35:31,560
lead the army to reclaim the City of Ayutthaya at all costs.

315
00:35:38,320 --> 00:35:40,600
I humbly accept your royal command, Your Majesty.

316
00:35:48,920 --> 00:35:52,640
In the middle of the 12th lunar month, Mingyi Swa

317
00:35:54,160 --> 00:35:58,080
led an army of two hundred thousand toward Ayutthaya.

318
00:36:04,317 --> 00:36:06,920
It is truly Your Highness's great wisdom

319
00:36:07,597 --> 00:36:09,240
to have changed the route of the army.

320
00:36:12,817 --> 00:36:13,920
I have calculated that

321
00:36:15,320 --> 00:36:17,880
by taking the route through the Three Pagodas Pass,

322
00:36:18,480 --> 00:36:21,800
we shall reach Ayutthaya swifter than the original path via Mae La Mao Pass.

323
00:36:25,170 --> 00:36:27,040
The troops will not be overly exhausted.

324
00:36:29,123 --> 00:36:31,800
You are truly most merciful.

325
00:36:32,450 --> 00:36:35,320
The morale of the soldiers this time is stronger than ever.

326
00:36:36,320 --> 00:36:38,680
We shall surely seize victory, Your Highness.

327
00:37:02,243 --> 00:37:04,160
I beg for your royal clemency, Your Majesty.

328
00:37:05,923 --> 00:37:07,490
Keep practicing your swords, do not stop.

329
00:37:07,850 --> 00:37:08,851
Yes, Your Majesty.

330
00:37:15,517 --> 00:37:16,640
Rise, Khao.

331
00:37:17,717 --> 00:37:20,480
between us brothers, let there be no formality.

332
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:22,481
Yes, Your Majesty.

333
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:30,360
What is it? Speak your mind.

334
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:32,920
The scouts have reported that

335
00:37:33,640 --> 00:37:35,160
the Crown Prince's army

336
00:37:35,357 --> 00:37:37,000
has already entered through the Three Pagodas Pass.

337
00:37:43,243 --> 00:37:46,320
Since it cannot be avoided, let us march out to meet them.

338
00:37:46,800 --> 00:37:48,521
Do not let the battle come too close to the capital.

339
00:37:54,000 --> 00:37:56,160
Phet, Sri, Duang.

340
00:37:56,363 --> 00:37:57,364
Yes, Your Majesty.

341
00:38:01,637 --> 00:38:02,720
Prepare the troops.

342
00:38:03,200 --> 00:38:05,080
We shall march out to intercept the Hongsawadi army.

343
00:38:05,917 --> 00:38:07,240
I humbly accept your royal command, Your Majesty.

344
00:38:13,597 --> 00:38:15,400
I wish to train with you all. Come on.

345
00:38:35,280 --> 00:38:36,760
While I was in Hongsawadi,

346
00:38:37,737 --> 00:38:39,280
I secretly bribed the Brahmins

347
00:38:39,800 --> 00:38:42,801
to copy the horoscope of the Crown Prince and kept it,

348
00:38:43,703 --> 00:38:45,000
thinking that one day it would be useful.

349
00:38:57,280 --> 00:38:59,160
Your excellency possesses profound knowledge.

350
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:04,000
Please examine and compare his horoscope with that of my elder brother.

351
00:39:07,590 --> 00:39:10,720
Should the two of them come face to face,

352
00:39:12,283 --> 00:39:13,284
what would the outcome be?

353
00:39:44,680 --> 00:39:45,681
What is it, Your Excellency?

354
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,360
I have marched the army out of Ayutthaya

355
00:39:58,920 --> 00:40:01,240
to await the Hongsawadi forces,

356
00:40:02,240 --> 00:40:04,000
but having barely passed the city gates,

357
00:40:04,880 --> 00:40:06,160
ill news has arrived.

358
00:40:11,330 --> 00:40:13,800
May it please Your Majesty, Phraya Phetphichai requests an audience.

359
00:40:24,480 --> 00:40:26,760
Now that you are the director of the palace guard department,

360
00:40:27,200 --> 00:40:28,360
why have you come all this way?

361
00:40:29,440 --> 00:40:30,880
Or has something occurred within the capital?

362
00:40:33,577 --> 00:40:34,720
Not at all, Your Majesty.

363
00:40:35,457 --> 00:40:38,723
Phra Maha Thera Khanchong has consecrated the protective charms,

364
00:40:39,203 --> 00:40:40,960
but due to his old age, he had forgotten them.

365
00:40:41,237 --> 00:40:42,961
Thus, he commanded me to present them to Your Majesty.

366
00:40:52,770 --> 00:40:53,800
Thank you very much.

367
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:55,881
Sri.

368
00:40:56,950 --> 00:40:58,160
Take the lord

369
00:40:58,600 --> 00:41:00,720
and distribute the protective charms to the soldiers.

370
00:41:02,320 --> 00:41:03,440
Yes, Your Majesty.

371
00:41:12,870 --> 00:41:15,680
Come quickly to receive the protective charms from Phra Maha Thera Khanchong.

372
00:41:17,163 --> 00:41:18,164
Those over there, come forward.

373
00:41:35,490 --> 00:41:36,491
Take these and distribute them.

374
00:41:36,920 --> 00:41:38,440
Give them to the others, too. Be careful.

375
00:41:39,390 --> 00:41:40,720
Here, take some for the others as well.

376
00:42:15,883 --> 00:42:17,960
What is the matter? Please speak.

377
00:42:19,440 --> 00:42:22,720
His Majesty has engaged in battle with the Crown Prince many times,

378
00:42:23,490 --> 00:42:25,320
and each time, their side was defeated.

379
00:42:26,040 --> 00:42:29,200
Yet, the Crown Prince has never sustained even the slightest injury.

380
00:42:29,443 --> 00:42:30,445
As you all have seen,

381
00:42:33,670 --> 00:42:35,800
both sides have avoided harming one another.

382
00:42:38,040 --> 00:42:40,440
Having followed His Majesty since he was young,

383
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:44,000
I know well that the two of them love each other like brothers,

384
00:42:44,610 --> 00:42:46,840
and they have supported one another on many occasions.

385
00:42:48,240 --> 00:42:49,920
King Nanda Bayin knows this well.

386
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:52,120
That is why he sent the crown prince,

387
00:42:52,743 --> 00:42:54,680
knowing that His Majesty would stay his hand.

388
00:42:55,880 --> 00:42:58,160
If neither side dares to strike, then so be it.

389
00:42:59,410 --> 00:43:00,600
But if in the days to come,

390
00:43:01,400 --> 00:43:03,160
he change his mind and strike first,

391
00:43:03,960 --> 00:43:05,161
shall we not be at a disadvantage

392
00:43:11,200 --> 00:43:14,400
What would you have us do then?

393
00:43:14,880 --> 00:43:15,881
Please speak your mind.

394
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:20,000
Prince Ekathosarot is deeply concerned for his brother,

395
00:43:20,577 --> 00:43:23,480
thus has commanded me to follow him to pay respects to Phra Maha Thera Khanchong.

396
00:43:27,323 --> 00:43:28,840
The heavens are on our side now.

397
00:43:30,690 --> 00:43:31,691
What is it, Your Holiness?

398
00:43:34,070 --> 00:43:38,480
As for the horoscope of Crown Prince Mingyi Swa,

399
00:43:40,050 --> 00:43:41,400
from this year

400
00:43:42,550 --> 00:43:43,920
until the next,

401
00:43:47,320 --> 00:43:48,840
he shall face a great misfortune,

402
00:43:56,430 --> 00:43:58,360
one that may even prove fatal.

403
00:43:59,303 --> 00:44:00,304
- What?
- What?

404
00:44:01,920 --> 00:44:03,200
Is his horoscope truly so fatal?

405
00:45:31,243 --> 00:45:32,700
It is nothing but the idle chatter of birds.

406
00:45:33,370 --> 00:45:34,371
Pish!

407
00:45:34,883 --> 00:45:36,160
Muy taught me that,

408
00:45:36,640 --> 00:45:38,297
though it may sound like the idle chatter of birds,

409
00:45:38,563 --> 00:45:42,183
when one is lost in the forest, it can be used as a signal to find each other.

410
00:45:42,577 --> 00:45:43,578
Is that so?

411
00:45:45,240 --> 00:45:46,480
Then teach me as well.

412
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:54,880
Perhaps in the days to come, we shall signal one another.

413
00:45:56,397 --> 00:45:57,398
Of course.

414
00:45:58,440 --> 00:45:59,441
Spread the leaf.

415
00:46:01,457 --> 00:46:02,280
Fold it down.

416
00:46:03,557 --> 00:46:04,558
Like this.

417
00:46:06,730 --> 00:46:07,731
Blow.

418
00:46:13,970 --> 00:46:15,160
Blow steadily.

419
00:47:28,810 --> 00:47:32,000
I was still wondering whether or not you would come.

420
00:47:34,277 --> 00:47:35,700
When I first heard the sound,

421
00:47:36,863 --> 00:47:38,320
I could hardly believe my ears.

422
00:47:42,677 --> 00:47:44,040
But I had to come and see for myself.

423
00:47:45,757 --> 00:47:47,000
If there is something on your mind, speak.

424
00:47:49,560 --> 00:47:51,500
I have something important to tell you.

425
00:47:56,610 --> 00:47:58,000
Is his horoscope truly so fatal?

426
00:47:59,770 --> 00:48:01,200
Phra Maha Thera Khanchong has prophesied that,

427
00:48:01,900 --> 00:48:03,440
between this year and the next,

428
00:48:04,277 --> 00:48:07,440
the Crown Prince shall surely perish on the battlefield.

429
00:48:10,510 --> 00:48:11,511
Am I

430
00:48:14,503 --> 00:48:15,720
to die then?

431
00:48:32,060 --> 00:48:33,161
What of it?

432
00:48:35,477 --> 00:48:36,800
Who is born that does not die?

433
00:48:39,160 --> 00:48:40,600
Do you not believe me?

434
00:48:44,443 --> 00:48:45,445
I believe you.

435
00:48:49,870 --> 00:48:51,120
Thank you for coming to tell me.

436
00:48:56,770 --> 00:48:57,920
But I am a general.

437
00:48:59,360 --> 00:49:03,000
Even if I know the outcome, I must fight until my dying breath.

438
00:49:10,150 --> 00:49:11,151
At the very least,

439
00:49:14,497 --> 00:49:16,480
it shall please my father

440
00:49:19,483 --> 00:49:22,640
- for he honors those who die on the battlefield as the truly brave.
- Brother.

441
00:49:25,240 --> 00:49:27,077
Hongsawadi does not lack brave men,

442
00:49:27,630 --> 00:49:29,201
but it lacks a righteous king.

443
00:49:32,640 --> 00:49:35,400
You must preserve your life and wait for the day you ascend to the throne.

444
00:49:36,441 --> 00:49:37,800
For only you

445
00:49:38,640 --> 00:49:41,440
can extinguish the fires of war and bring peace to the realm.

446
00:49:54,690 --> 00:49:55,691
Very well,

447
00:49:58,343 --> 00:49:59,400
I shall be careful.

448
00:49:59,840 --> 00:50:00,841
I do not trust this.

449
00:50:02,917 --> 00:50:03,918
Is that so?

450
00:50:06,120 --> 00:50:07,121
And for what reason?

451
00:50:09,030 --> 00:50:11,031
Prince Ekathosarot has issued a royal command

452
00:50:12,103 --> 00:50:13,520
for me to inform you all.

453
00:50:14,240 --> 00:50:17,400
In this upcoming battle, he asked that the three of you

454
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:19,600
unite your hearts and strength

455
00:50:20,101 --> 00:50:22,702
to slay the Crown Prince by any means necessary.

456
00:50:26,630 --> 00:50:27,640
On the battlefield,

457
00:50:28,240 --> 00:50:30,600
you and I have always spared one another.

458
00:50:31,450 --> 00:50:32,451
But this time,

459
00:50:33,040 --> 00:50:36,080
I cannot command others to spare you, for the troops would lose heart.

460
00:50:42,920 --> 00:50:44,200
Then do not spare me.

461
00:50:45,957 --> 00:50:47,040
Let happen what may.

462
00:50:51,090 --> 00:50:52,640
Do you truly not believe me?

463
00:51:06,520 --> 00:51:08,240
I may not fond of war,

464
00:51:12,863 --> 00:51:14,240
But I am no coward.

465
00:51:16,357 --> 00:51:17,358
Brother.

466
00:51:47,200 --> 00:51:48,201
I am sorry.

467
00:52:30,077 --> 00:52:32,440
Perhaps Phra Maha Thera Khanchong’s prophecy was mistaken.

468
00:52:34,103 --> 00:52:36,720
Maybe it is not I who must die in this battle.

469
00:52:37,057 --> 00:52:38,440
If I must die

470
00:52:39,840 --> 00:52:41,400
by your hand,

471
00:52:49,197 --> 00:52:50,720
I shall have no regrets.
